sentences.sContent: Our school has been reprieved from insufficient financial resources.
sentences.sContent_eng: Our school has been reprieved from insufficient financial resources.
sentences.sCn: 我们学校财力不足的困境现已暂时得到缓解。

sentences.sContent: So, initially as you looked at it it was associated with insufficient coolant.
sentences.sContent_eng: So, initially as you looked at it it was associated with insufficient coolant.
sentences.sCn: 所以，最初你们观察它时，它是与,不足的冷却剂有关。

sentences.sContent: Some people like to track everything, and we do imagine that it could be helpful to see longer periods of poor or insufficient sleep than we realized we were experiencing.
sentences.sContent_eng: Some people like to track everything, and we do imagine that it could be helpful to see longer periods of poor or insufficient sleep than we realized we were experiencing.
sentences.sCn: 有些人喜欢追踪记录所有的事情，我们可以想象，了解我们睡眠不足或睡眠质量差的时间比我们意识到的长，会对我们有帮助。

words.tran: 不足，不充分；机能不全；不适当

trans.tranCn: 不足的，不充足的；不胜任的；缺乏能力的
trans.tranOther: not enough, or not great enough
